Olive oil choc chip banana bread muffins bc a good life is eating healthy but balanced :) I’ll never stop eating my sweet treats 

Ingredients: (makes 6 muffins)
1 large bananas 1 eggs 1/4 cup olive oil 1/2 tsp vanilla 1/4 cup + 2 tbsp maple syrup 1 cups flour 3/4 tsp baking powder 1/4 tsp baking soda Pinch of salt 1 tsp cinnamon 1 bar chopped dark choc (made with coconut sugar)

Directions:
1. Preheat the oven to 425. Mash bananas. Mix with eggs, maple syrup, vanilla, and olive oil.
2. To the same bowl, add the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon, and stir until flour mixture is just combined. Fold in the chopped chocolate if using.
3. Pour the mixture into a greased or lined muffin pan and bake for 5 minutes at 425 then reduce the temperature to 350 and bake for another 15-20 minutes. ENJOY!

10 minute ginger debloat noodles that can be eaten hot or cold 🍜 just add your fav protein on the side and you’re good to go! These are so good to debloat or keep your gut feeling good

Makes one serving:
1 serving rice noodles
1-2 tbsp olive oil (or other)
1 tbsp maple syrup
1 tbsp soy sauce/tamari
1 inch fresh ginger
1 clove garlic
2 tbsp green onion (green and white parts)
sesame seeds
English cucumber (optional)

Directions:
1. Peel the ginger and dice into thin slices. Chop the garlic and cucumber into thin slices, and chop the green onion. Cook your noodles according to the package. Add the noodles to ice water for cold noodles, or just drain. 
2. In the meantime, add the maple, soy sauce, and onions to your serving bowl. 
3. Add the oil to a pan over medium heat. Once hot, add the garlic and ginger and cook for 3 minutes, then turn off the heat. Remove the ginger and garlic from the oil, and pour the oil into your serving bowl with the other ingredients. Mix with a splash of water until everything is emulsified. 
4. Once everything is mixed, add the drained noodles on top of the sauce and mix together. Top with the sliced cucumber, sesame seeds, and more green onion. Enjoy my friends !!

this salad plus fresh rice and your favorite protein = perfection 🤩 cucumbers are one of my favorite veggies ever when my gut needs to debloat or a little break!

Ingredients:
1 English cucumber
2 tbsp peanut butter
1 tbsp lime juice
1 tsp rice vinegar
1 tbsp maple syrup
1 tbsp soy sauce/tamari
1 tbsp full fat coconut milk/coconut cream
sesame seeds
green onion (optional)

Directions:
1. Chop cucumber and the green parts of the green onion if using. 
2. Mix the peanut butter, lime juice, rice vinegar, maple, soy sauce, and coconut together until the sauce is completely combined. 
3. Pour over the cucumbers and mix well. Top with lots of sesame seeds and the green onion. Enjoy 🫶

Salt and (apple cider) vinegar potatoes in a Greek style potato salad. The goal is to make everything as nourishing as possible :) 

Ingredients:
1 bag baby potatoes (any kind)
6 tbsp ACV
olive oil 
salt
pepper
1 tbsp butter (optional)
handful olives
1/4-1/2 red onion
1/4 c dill
handful feta

Directions:
1. Chop potatoes and olives in half, thinly slice onion, and chop dill. Heat a large splash of oil in a pan over medium heat. Once hot, add the potatoes and season with salt and pepper to taste. Sauté occasionally for 5 min.
2. Decrease the heat to low, add half the ACV, butter, and a splash of water. Cover for 12-15 minutes.
3. Uncover and bring the heat back to medium high. Add the remaining apple cider vinegar and sauté for 5 more minutes.
4. Immediately toss with more salt to taste, then combine with the olives, onion, dill, and feta. Enjoy 🫶

4 habits for better gut health that I still practice to this day:
- low impact movement esp Pilates 
- eat probiotics and fiber, + high protein breakfast
- morning sunlight 
- circadian fasting (don’t eat too late at night and try to fast 12 hours from dinner to breakfast)

Sweet potato brownies but they’re the fudgiest brownies you’ve ever had and you can’t even taste the sweet potato. So perfect when the chocolate cravings hit before your period 🤭

Ingredients:
1/2 c baked and mashed sweet potato
1/4 c maple syrup
2 tbsp oil
1 tbsp almond butter
1 tsp vanilla extract
1 single shot espresso
28g cocoa powder (1/4 c + 1 tbsp)
21g flour
1 tsp baking powder
1/4 tsp salt
chocolate chips/chopped chocolate

Directions:
1. Bake the sweet potato at 400 degrees for 55-60 minutes, or until it is completely cooked and soft. Let it cool, then remove the skin and mash until smooth. 
2. Combine with the maple sryup, oil, almond butter, vanilla, and espresso. Then, add the flour, baking powder, and salt. Fold in the chocolate chips last.
3. Bake at 350 for 12-15 minutes. Let it cool to room temperature before cutting into 6 equal pieces. Enjoyyyy 🍠🍫

the cleanest yummiest cinnamon roll banana bread you’ll ever eat 💫 made it with olive oil for extra nutrition and you can make it gluten free too!

Ingredients:
3 bananas
2 c flour
2 eggs
1/2 c olive oil
1/2 c maple syrup
1 tsp vanilla
1 1/2 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp baking soda
1/4 tsp salt
1/3 c coconut sugar
2 tsp cinnamon
4 tbsp butter (or sub for df butter/coconut oil)

Directions:
1. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees.
2. Mash the bananas, then combine with the eggs, olive oil, maple syrup, and vanilla. In a separate bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt. Then, add the wet ingredients to the dry and mix until just combined.
3. Melt the butter, then combine with the coconut sugar and cinnamon. Once it has cooled slightly, add half the batter to your loaf pan, and pour half the cinnamon sugar mixture on top. Pour in the remaining batter, then cinnamon sugar on top, and swirl with a knife.
4. Bake for 55-60 minutes. Enjoyyyyyy my friends xoxo

making our fav desserts healthier for you since ‘22 🤠 super easy and gut healthy carrot cake loaf. no refined sugar, can be made gf/df, and I use olive oil in this recipe :)

Ingredients:
2 c flour
1 c shredded carrot
1 banana
3/4 c coconut sugar
2 eggs
1/4 c oil
1/4 c milk
2 tsp baking powder
1/4 tsp baking soda
1 tsp vanilla
2 tsp cinnamon
1/4 tsp salt

Directions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
2. Mash the banana and shred the carrot, then combine with the eggs, oil, vanilla, and coconut sugar. 
3. In a separate bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, and salt. Then, add the wet ingredients to the dry, and add in the milk as well. Mix until just combined.
4. Transfer the batter to a loaf pan and bake for 35-40 minutes. Enjoy 🥕👩‍🌾✨
